replyContent:
The pathway can be different on every device, but this should work for Samsung. Let me know if not.

Support@m2catalyst.com.

1. Go to your device SETTINGS.
2. Tap WALLPAPERS AND THEMES
3. Tap VIEW ALL in the My Wallpapers section.
4. Tap the settings icon at the top right corner of the screen and tap Live Wallpapers.
5. Tap Phases of the Moon.

This is a fun little app for seeing a snapshot of the Moon's current status.  Great for the space geek and for educating curious minds about how the phases of the moon progress.  Price is great especially considering it is a fund-raising tool for a very informative website.
Picked this up after a great Live Astronomy hangout. Works great on Droid 3 and is probably one of the best looking apps I've even used.

This app just shows the phase of the moon, now and in the future and the past.    Very nice graphics and a smooth and nice, intuitive way to slide the moon to  check future and past dates. I assume it is pretty accurate too :-)    Well worth the small fee!

Great idea for a touch screen app.  Being able to slowly slide through daily phases or quickly through the weeks/months is an excellent way to look ahead or back in the lunar calendar.  The developer is actively engaged in improving existing features and considering new ones.
Works really well on my Galaxy Nexus

Well worth the 0.99¬¢ If you are into Astronomy, or just want to know the fazes of the moon, what % it is illuminated, how far away it if from Earth, and how old it is in its cycle ( Or wish to check out how it will wax or wane in the future or past with a simple swipe of your hand ) get your hands on this app.

Love how I can seamlessly move from night to night and watch how the Moon changes.  The real images show not only the phases, but the Moon's libration as well. Works like a charm on my Motorola Droid 4. I find myself playing with it often and have been showing it off to others.  Looking forward to more features with updates, such as Moonrise and set times.
Amazing images of the current moon phase. Easily slide from day to day and watch the terminator move. Works great on droid bionic.
Works great on my LG LS855 phone.  I love the the fact that the moon looks photo realistic.  The librations and apparent size of the moon from day to day seem very precise.  Animation is very smooth.
Very helpful ...runs very smooth.  Nice!

This is a really lively application that does a simple job well. I initially installed just out of curiosity, haven seen a few apps like this in the past but was surprised by how much better this app is than all the rest. The animation is so smooth and inviting, I spent a long time just sliding the phases along. I also love how the correct tilt of the moon is displayed and animated.  If you're into astronomy, then this is a must have app and puts any other moon phase app to shame.
Samsung Galaxy Tab 2 7.0 (ICS)  Works great! Smoothly slides through beautiful representations of the phases. Very nice!

I ran this app on my droid 1 running CyanogenMod 7.1.0 and on my razor running ICS.  Very smooth, high quality phase transitions on both when you flick between days/weeks.  The "today" and "next full moon" buttons are really useful if you get too sucked into browsing the moon phases and definitely get the job done if you want to know the information you probably loaded the app in the first place for.  Next up: the devs are fine tuning the scrolling and working on using your permissions to synchronize moon data with your location (anticipating this happening and working well, I am giving the app 5 stars).
Performs superbly!
Super smooth, awesome graphics, shows everything you need. Definetely worth it!

Now I know. Swiping the moon through its phases is illuminating, entertaining and educational.  Beautifully rendered moon makes it a pleasure.
